22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Two%20Weeks%20After%20Surrender%2C%20Bilkis%20Bano%20Case%20Convict%20Out%20on%20Five-Day%20Parole%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09152825%2FUntitled-design-3-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EJust%20two%20weeks%20after%20the%2011%20men%20convicted%20for%20gang-raping%20Bilkis%20Bano%20and%20killing%20several%20members%20of%20her%20family%20during%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20pogrom%20were%20told%20to%20surrender%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20one%20of%20the%20convicts%2C%20Pradip%20Modhiya%2C%20was%20released%20on%20Wednesday%20on%20a%20five-day%20parole%20granted%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court.%20Modhiya%20was%20allowed%20to%20return%20to%20his%20village%20of%20Randhikpur%20in%20Dahod%20district%20because%20of%20his%20father%20in%20law%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fin-law-dead-bilkis-bano-case-convict-out-on-parole-a-fortnight-after-surrender-9152122%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convicts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fall-11-convicts-in-bilkis-bano-case-surrender%5C%22%3Ehad%20surrendered%3C%2Fa%3E%20late%20on%20January%2021%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20M.R.%20Mengdey%20had%20on%20February%205%20allowed%20Modhiya%20parole%20from%20February%207%20to%2011.%20In%20his%20plea%2C%20Modhiya%20had%20asked%20for%2030-day%20parole%2C%20with%20his%20lawyers%20saying%20it%20was%20to%20his%20credit%20that%20he%20had%20%E2%80%9Creported%20back%20on%20time%E2%80%9D%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20orders%20and%20his%20behaviour%20in%20jail%20was%20also%20said%20to%20be%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20Superintendent%20of%20Police%20Vishakha%20Jain%20from%20Limkheda%20in%20Dahod%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20HC%20has%20granted%20parole%20to%20the%20convict%20and%20he%20has%20returned%20to%20his%20village%20for%20five%20days.%20As%20per%20his%20parole%20conditions%2C%20he%20is%20not%20required%20to%20report%20to%20the%20Randhikpur%20police%20station%E2%80%A6%20The%20district%20police%20has%20no%20role%20to%20perform%20during%20the%20parole%20period.%20He%20is%20expected%20to%20return%20on%20his%20own%20to%20jail.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20earlier%20stint%20in%20prison%20in%20the%20case%20since%20January%202008%2C%20before%20the%20Gujarat%20government%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20decision%20to%20grant%20all%20the%20convicts%20premature%20release%2C%20Modhiya%20had%20been%20let%20out%20on%20parole%20for%201%2C041%20and%20on%20furlough%20for%20another%20223%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbilkis-bano-supreme-court-gujarat-not-competent-remission%5C%22%3Ecame%20down%20heavily%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20for%20granting%20premature%20release%20to%20the%2011%20convicts.%20The%20bench%20said%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Gujarat%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20complicity%20with%20the%20convicts%E2%80%9D%20and%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20this%20very%20apprehension%20which%20led%20this%20Court%20to%20transfer%20the%20trial%20out%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20to%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gujarat%20government%20%E2%80%93%20under%20the%20same%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20which%20was%20in%20power%20during%20the%20riots%20%E2%80%93%20had%20announced%20the%20decision%20to%20grant%20the%2011%20men%20premature%20release%20on%20August%2015%2C%20Independence%20Day%2C%20in%202022.%20Granting%20remission%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20had%20said%20that%20this%20decision%20had%20been%20arrived%20at%20by%20a%20panel%20it%20had%20set%20up%2C%20comprising%20officials%20and%20%E2%80%98social%20workers%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20whom