2Fsupreme-court-test-for-bail-under-uapa-khalistani-terror-movement-248970%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Process%20is%20punishment%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20that%20mere%20delay%20of%20trial%20is%20not%20adequate%20grounds%20to%20grant%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fuapa-case-data-process-punishment-home-ministry-rajya-sabha%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20on%20how%20figures%20released%20by%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20backed%20up%20the%20belief%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98process%20is%20the%20punishment%E2%80%99%20when%20cases%20are%20registered%20under%20the%20UAPA.%20Government%20data%20revealed%20that%2097.5%25%20of%20people%20arrested%20under%20the%20anti-terror%20law%20%E2%80%93%20which%20makes%20obtaining%20bail%20virtually%20impossible%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20imprisoned%20for%20multiple%20years%20while%20waiting%20for%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20case%20in%20point%20is%20student%20leader%20Umar%20Khalid%2C%20arrested%20in%20September%202020%20under%20the%20UAPA.%20His%20bail%20hearing%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fa-timeline-of-umar-khalids-bail-hearings%5C%22%3Edelayed%20for%20the%2014th%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20his%20four-year-long%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20against%20what%20the%20apex%20court%20itself%20has%20termed%20as%20a%20norm%20of%20%E2%80%98bail%2C%20not%20jail%2C%E2%80%99%20the%20bench%20said%20on%20February%208%20in%20a%20judgment%20authored%20by%20Justice%20Kumar%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20conventional%20idea%20in%20bail%20jurisprudence%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20ordinary%20penal%20offences%20that%20the%20discretion%20of%20Courts%20must%20tilt%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20oft-quoted%20phrase%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98bail%20is%20the%20rule%2C%20jail%20is%20the%20exception%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20unless%20circumstances%20justify%20otherwise%20%E2%80%93%20does%20not%20find%20any%20place%20while%20dealing%20with%20bail%20applications%20under%20UAP%20Act.%20The%20%E2%80%98exercise%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20general%20power%20to%20grant%20bail%20under%20the%20UAP%20Act%20is%20severely%20restrictive%20in%20scope.%20The%20form%20of%20the%20words%20used%20in%20proviso%20to%20Section%2043D%20(5)%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98shall%20not%20be%20released%E2%80%99%20in%20contrast%20with%20the%20form%20of%20the%20words%20as%20found%20in%20Section%20437(1)%20CrPC%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98may%20be%20released%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20suggests%20the%20intention%20of%20the%20Legislature%20to%20make%20bail%2C%20the%20exception%20and%20jail%2C%20the%20rule%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Bail%2C%20not%20jail%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20often%20highlighted%20that%20bail%20should%20be%20the%20rule%20and%20jail%20an%20exception.%20The%20principle%20was%20first%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20apex%20court%20during%20the%20landmark%20judgment%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F8258%2F%5C%22%3EState%20of%20Rajasthan%20V.%20Balchand%20alias%20Baliay%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ecase%20in%201978%20%2Cwhen%20Justice%20V.R.%20Krishna%20Iyer%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20basic%20rule%20may%20perhaps%20be%20tersely%20put%20as%20%E2%80%98bail%2C%20not%20jail%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Sundresh%20and%20Kumar%20bench%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20if%20a%20court%20arrives%20at%20a%20conclusion%20after%20hearing%20a%20public%20prosecutor%20and%20looking%20at%20the%20case%20diary%20that%20there%20are%20grounds%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20accusations%20against%20an%20accused%20are%20prima%20facie%20true%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbail%20must%20be%20rejected%20as%20a%20rule.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20only%20if%20the%20test%20for%20rejection%20of%20bail%20is%20not%20satisfied%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20Courts%20would%20proceed%20to%20decide%20the%20bail%20application%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98tripod%20test%E2%80%99%20(flight%20risk%2C%20influencing%20witnesses%2C%20tampering%20with%20evidence)%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Kumar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20obtaining%20bail%20is%20nearly%20impossible%20when%20a%20person%20is%20arrested%20under%20the%20UAPA%2C%20in%20a%202022%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fumar-khalid-jyoti-jagtap-bail-order-judicial-lottery-liberty%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20legal%20scholar%20Gautam%20Bhatia%20had%20referred%20to%20an%20innate%20inconsistency%20in%20bail%20judgments%20under%20UAPA%20within%20the%20same%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707460231000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F12175442%2Fuapa.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbail-an-exception-jail-is-rule-in-uapa-cases-how-the-sc-went-against-its-own-dictum%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Government%20data%20revealed%20in%202022%20that%2097.5%25%20of%20people%20arrested%20under%20the%20anti-terror%20law%20%E2%80%93%20which%20makes%20obtaining%20bail%20virtually%20impossible%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20imprisoned%20for%20multiple%20years%20while%20waiting%20for%20trial.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbail-an-exception-jail-is-rule-in-uapa-cases-how-the-sc-went-against-its-own-dictum%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Not%20in%20the%20Name%20of%20Gender%20Justice%3A%20Reflections%20on%20Uttarakhand's%20UCC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09110758%2Flewis-j-goetz-67heLkXJ340-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20much%20touted%2C%20much%20awaited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fcivil-code-bill-english0001-520761.pdf%5C%22%3EUttarakhand%20Bill%20on%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%3C%2Fa%3E%20(UCC)%20has%20been%20passed.%20It%20seeks%20to%20unify%20family%20laws%2C%20spanning%20issues%20of%20marriage%20and%20divorce%20and%20their%20registration%2C%20restitution%20of%20conjugal%20rights%20and%20judicial%20separation%2C%20nullity%20of%20marriage%20and%20divorce%2C%20maintenance%2C%20alimony%20and%20custody%2C%20intestate%20and%20testamentary%20succession%2C%20and%20live-in%20relationships.%20Adoption%2C%20guardianship%20and%20surrogacy%20are%20conspicuous%20by%20their%20absence.%20In%20the%20past%20decades%2C%20the%20UCC%20has%20been%20projected%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20achieve%20%3Cem%3Enari%20shakti%3C%2Fem%3E%20(empowerment%20of%20women)%20and%20gender%20justice%20was%20seen%20to%20be%20the%20goal%2C%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fbjp-ucc-with-gender-justice-discrimination-personal-laws%5C%22%3Eequating%20uniformity%20with%20equality.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20claim%20will%20be%20examined%20in%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20underlying%20presumption%20in%20family%20law%20is%20that%20marriages%20and%20intimate%20relationships%20are%20consensual%2C%20that%20they%20protect%20the%20constitutionally%20guaranteed%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20dignity%20of%20the%20parties%20concerned%2C%20and%20that%20the%20agency%20and%20decisional%20autonomy%20exercised%20by%20the%20concerned%20parties%20are%20acknowledged%20and%20protected.%20However%2C%20some%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20are%20a%20cause%20of%20grave%20concern%20as%20they%20violate%20this%20fundamental%20principle.%20Three%20such%20provisions%20are%20highlighted%20and%20analysed%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegistration%20of%20marriages%2C%20divorces%20and%20live-in%20relationships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%2C%20through%20clause%206%2C%20makes%20it%20mandatory%20for%20marriages%20to%20be%20registered%20subsequent%20to%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20Code%2C%20if%20the%20marriage%20takes%20place%20in%20Uttarakhand%20or%20one%20of%20the%20parties%20is%20a%20resident%20of%20the%20state.%20Clause%207%20makes%20it%20mandatory%20for%20marriages%20performed%20from%202010%20(when%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhighcourtofuttarakhand.gov.in%2Ffiles%2FCompulsory_Registration_of_Marriage_Act_2010.pdf%5C%22%3EUttarakhand%20Compulsory%20Registration%20of%20Marriage%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20enacted)%20to%20the%20commencement%20of%20this%20Code%2C%20to%20be%20registered%2C%20unless%20it%20has%20already%20been%20registered%20under%20the%202010%20Act.%20Even%20when%20claims%20of%20curtailing%20child%20marriage%20and%20bigamy%20have%20been%20made%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20movement%20in%20India%20has%20been%20reluctant%20to%20support%20mandatory%20registration%20of%20marriages%2C%20as%20the%20penal%20sanction%20and%20civil%20consequences%20attached%20to%20a%20failure%20to%20register%2C%20would%20disproportionately%20impact%20women.%20This%20is%20more%20so%20due%20to%20lower%20awareness%20of%20rights%20and%20law%20among%20them%2C%20and%20the%20power%20differentials%20between%20the%20spouses.%20Placing%20the%20onus%20of%20registration%20on%20women%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20poor%20and%20illiterate%2C%20with%20no%20corresponding%20legal%20mandate%20of%20the%20state%20to%20create%20awareness%20of%20the%20same%2C%20seems%20unfair%20and%20unjust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20registration%20of%20decrees%20of%20divorce%20and%20nullity%20passed%20after%20and%20before%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20Code%20are%20also%20to%20be%20mandatorily%20registered%2C%20as%20per%20clauses%208%20and%209%20respectively.%20Since%20these%20are%20passed%20by%20courts%20(both%20within%20Uttarakhand%20and%20outside%20Uttarakhand%20with%20at%20least%20one%20party%20as%20a%20resident%20of%20the%20state)%2C%20there%20could%20be%20a%20mechanism%20created%20that%20links%20the%20Registry%20with%20the%20courts%2C%20particularly%20as%20most%20courts%20are%20being%20digitised%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1896034%5C%22%3EUnion%20government%E2%80%99s%20initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rather%20than%20placing%20the%20onus%20on%20the%20individuals%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20non-registration%20will%20not%20affect%20the%20validity%20of%20a%20marriage%2C%20as%20per%20clause%2020%2C%20failure%20to%20register%20marriage%2C%20decrees%20of%20nullity%20and%20divorce%20would%20result%20in%20penal%20consequences%20%E2%80%93%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%2025%2C000%2C%20as%20per%20clause%2018(2).%20This%20is%20indeed%20very%20steep.%20One%20cannot%20imagine%20the%20predicament%20of%20poor%20and%20illiterate%20women%20who%20would%20be%20compelled%20to%20navigate%20administrative%20mechanisms%20for%20registration%2C%20and%20face%20the%20penal%20consequences%20upon%20their%20failure%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20registers%20of%20marriage%2C%20nullity%20and%20divorce%20are%20open%20for%20public%20inspection%2C%20as%20per%20clause%2015.%20In%20a%20country%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdehradun%2Fmother-son-neighbour-get-life-for-killing-woman%2Farticleshow%2F103545962.cms%5C%22%3E(and%20state)%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20rampant%20honour%20crimes%2C%20and%20parents%E2%80%99%20and%20communities%E2%80%99%20resistance%20to%20inter-caste%2C%20inter-religious%20and%20inter-class%20marriages%2C%20such%20public%20inspection%20is%20likely%20to%20exacerbate%20the%20situation%20of%20vulnerability%20of%20adult%20women%20in%20choice%20marriages%20without%20parental%20approval%2C%20and%20make%20them%20target%20of%20attacks.%20Public%20inspection%20of%20such%20registers%20would%20facilitate%20moral%20policing%20and%20tighten%20the%20stranglehold%20of%20the%20natal%20family%20on%20young%20women%20who%20exercise%20choice%20and%20autonomy%20in%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20mandates%20persons%20in%20live-in%20relationships%20within%20the%20state%2C%20irrespective%20of%20whether%20or%20not%20they%20are%20residents%20of%20the%20state%2C%20to%20submit%20a%20statement%20of%20live-in%20relationship%20to%20the%20concerned%20Registrar%20(clause%20378).%20This%20provision%20is%20justified%20through%20the%20murder%20of%20young%20women%20by%20their%20partner%20in%20a%20live-in%20relationship%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20such%20as%20Shraddha%20Walkar%2C%20Nikki%20Yadav%20and%20Megha%20Thorvi.%20However%2C%20we%20need%20to%20pause%20and%20ask%20ourselves%20if%20this%20protectionist%20approach%20by%20a%20paternalistic%20state%20will%20truly%20empower%20women.%20Spotlight%20must%20be%20shone%20on%20the%20role%20of%20natal%20family%20in%20rejecting%20the%20woman%E2%80%99s%20choice%20of%20partner%2C%20thereby%20depriving%20her%20of%20a%20support%20system%20when%20the%20relationship%20turned%20violent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20failure%20to%20submit%20the%20statement%20within%20a%20month%20of%20commencement%20of%20the%20live-in%20relationship%2C%20entails%20imprisonment%20of%20up%20to%20three%20months%2C%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%2010%2C000%20or%20both%2C%20as%20per%20clause%20387(1).%20The%20disparity%20in%20the%20penal%20consequence%20between%20failure%20to%20register%20a%20marriage%20and%20failure%20to%20register%20a%20live-in%20relationship%2C%20with%20the%20latter%20entailing%20imprisonment%20in%20addition%20to%20fine%2C%20is%20glaring.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20statement%20is%20also%20required%20to%20be%20submitted%20to%20the%20Registrar%20upon%20termination%20of%20the%20live-in%20relationship%2C%20as%20per%20clause%20384.%20Upon%20such%20a%20submission%2C%20if%20either%20of%20the%20parties%20is%20below%2021%20years%20of%20age%2C%20the%20Registrar%20is%20also%20mandated%20to%20inform%20the%20parents%2Fguardians%20of%20the%20party%20regarding%20the%20same%2C%20as%20per%20clause%20385(3).%20This%20infantilises%20individuals%20aged%2018-21%20years%20who%20engage%20in%20such%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECumulatively%2C%20the%20chapter%20on%20live-in%20relationships%20compels%20adults%20living%20in%20consensual%20relationships%2C%20who%20may%20have%20deliberately%20avoided%20marriage%20and%20its%20legal%20consequences%2C%20to%20get%20enmeshed%20in%20administrative%20processes%2C%20thereby%20facilitating%20state%20scrutiny%20over%20them.%20As%20in%20the%20case%20of%20choice%20marriages%2C%20in%20live-in%20relationships%20too%2C%20this%20enables%20surveillance%2C%20moral%20policing%20and%20harassment%20by%20the%20natal%20family%2C%20community%20and%20possibly%2C%20the%20state%20machinery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20benefits%20available%20to%20those%20who%20register%20their%20live-in%20relationships%20are%20%E2%80%93%20avoidance%20of%20penal%20consequences%2C%20the%20woman%20can%20claim%20maintenance%20from%20her%20partner%20(under%20clause%20388)%2C%20and%20a%20child%20born%20from%20such%20a%20registered%20live-in%20relationship%20would%20be%20treated%20as%20legitimate%2C%20on%20par%20with%20other%20children%2C%20and%20consequently%20enjoy%20all%20rights%20including%20maintenance%20and%20property%20rights%20through%20intestate%20succession.%20It%20is%20unclear%20as%20to%20how%20these%20provisions%20would%20intersect%20with%20other%20legislations%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15436%2F1%2Fprotection_of_women_from_domestic_violence_act%252C_2005.pdf%5C%22%3EProtection%20of%20Women%20from%20Domestic%20Violence%20Act%2C%202005%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20seek%20to%20protect%2C%20among%20other%20categories%20of%20women%2C%20those%20in%20relationship%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20marriage.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20a%20woman%20fails%20to%20submit%20the%20mandated%20statement%20to%20the%20Registrar%2C%20whether%20she%20would%20be%20entitled%20to%20protection%20under%20the%20PWDVA%20is%20anyone%E2%80%99s%20guess.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20democratic%20country%2C%20adults%20living%20together%20in%20a%20consensual%20relationship%20ought%20not%20to%20be%20subjected%20to%20state%20monitoring%20through%20mandatory%20administrative%20procedures%2C%20in%20the%20guise%20of%20protecting%20the%20woman%20in%20the%20relationship.%20While%20society%20may%20frown%20upon%20or%20disapprove%20such%20relationships%2C%20such%20social%20morality%20ought%20not%20to%20colour%20a%20law.%20Through%20several%20judgments%2C%20the%20courts%20have%20affirmed%20the%20right%20of%20persons%20over%2018%20years%20of%20age%20to%20choose%20their%20intimate%20partner%2Fspouse%2C%20irrespective%20of%20caste%2C%20religious%20or%20other%20differences.%20These%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1364215%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELata%20Singh%20v.%20State%20of%20U.P.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1337458%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EArumugam%20Servai%20v.%20State%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F92846055%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EShakti%20Vahini%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F18303067%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EShafin%20Jahan%20v.%20Asokan%20K.M.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20provisions%20on%20compulsory%20registration%20of%20marriage%2C%20divorce%2C%20decree%20of%20nullity%20and%20commencement%20and%20termination%20of%20live-in%20relationships%20make%20a%20mockery%20out%20of%20such%20jurisprudence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetention%20of%20restitution%20of%20conjugal%20rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20has%20retained%20restitution%20of%20conjugal%20rights%20(RCR)%20as%20a%20matrimonial%C2%A0remedy%20at%20a%20time%20when%20its%20constitutional%20validity%20has%20been%20challenged%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Clause%2021%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20a%20copy%20paste%20of%20section%209%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%20and%20section%2022%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act.%20This%20is%20a%20regressive%20provision%20with%20colonial%20origin%2C%20that%20legally%20compels%20unwilling%20spouses%20to%20live%20together%20in%20the%20name%20of%20cohabitation%2C%20consortium%2C%20companionship%20and%20conjugality.%C2%A0Though%20on%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20it%20is%20a%20gender%20neutral%20provision%2C%20it%20has%20disproportionate%20and%20adverse%20ramifications%20for%20the%20wife%20who%20may%20be%20subjected%20to%20rape%20and%20forcible%20pregnancy%20by%20the%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20provision%20violates%20the%20right%20to%20live%20with%20dignity%2C%20bodily%20integrity%2C%20sexual%20autonomy%2C%20privacy%2C%20decisional%20autonomy%2C%20agency%20and%20reproductive%20rights%20and%20health%2C%20which%20every%20woman%2C%20including%20married%20women%2C%20are%20entitled%20to.%20Such%20rights%20%C2%A0have%20been%20upheld%20in%20various%20judgments.%20These%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F127517806%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJustice%20Puttuswamy%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(right%20to%20privacy)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F168671544%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENavtej%20Singh%20Johar%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(sexual%20autonomy)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F100550714%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELaxmi%20Mandal%20v.%20Deen%20Dayal%20Harinagar%20Hospital%20%26amp%3B%20Ors%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%20(access%20to%20reproductive%20health)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F157771%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESandesh%20Bansal%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(state%20responsibility%20in%20protecting%20and%20protecting%20women%E2%80%99s%20reproductive%20health)%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F123985596%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EX%20vs.%20Principal%20Secretary%20%E2%80%93%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Family%20Welfare%20Department%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(right%20of%20unmarried%20women%20and%20survivors%20of%20marital%20rape%20to%20terminate%20pregnancy).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20in%201983%2C%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20high%20court%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1987982%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ET.%20Sareetha%20vs.%20T.%20Venkata%20Subbiah%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20observed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20origin%20of%20this%20uncivilised%20remedy%20in%20our%20ancient%20country%20is%20only%20recent%20and%20is%20wholly%20illegitimate%E2%80%9D%20and%20further%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20decree%20for%20restitution%20of%20conjugal%20rights%20makes%20the%20unwilling%20victim%E2%80%99s%20body%20a%20soulless%20and%20a%20joyless%20vehicle%20for%20bringing%20into%20existence%20another%20human%20being.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20pregnancy%20would%20be%20foisted%20on%20her%20by%20the%20state%20and%20against%20her%20will.%E2%80%9D%20The%20%3Cem%3ET.%20Sareetha%20judgment%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20delivered%20close%20to%20a%20century%20after%20%3Cem%3ERukhmabai%20judgment%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20interrogated%20the%20same%20issue%20which%20is%20relevant%20even%20at%20present%20%E2%80%93%20the%20role%20of%20the%20state%20in%20interfering%20with%20sexual%20autonomy%20and%20bodily%20integrity%20of%20a%20woman%20within%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwcd.nic.in%2Fdocument%2Freport-high-level-committee-status-women-india-vol-3-june-2015%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%202015%20by%20a%20government-appointed%20high%20level%20committee%20on%20the%20status%20of%20women%2C%20it%20recommended%20that%20provisions%20related%20to%20RCR%20that%20exist%20in%20various%20statutes%20should%20be%20deleted.%20It%20reasoned%20out%20that%20the%20provision%20is%20only%20being%20used%20to%20defeat%20wife%E2%80%99s%20claim%20for%20maintenance%20and%20served%20little%20purpose%2C%20and%20had%20no%20place%20in%20independent%20India.%20Likewise%2C%20the%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.pib.gov.in%2Fdocuments%2Frlink%2F2018%2Faug%2Fp201883101.pdf%5C%22%3Econsultation%20paper%20on%20family%20law%20reforms%2C%20published%20in%202018%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recommended%20its%20deletion%20from%20the%20statute%20books.%20The%20Uttarakhand%20Bill%20turned%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20these%20recommendations%2C%20and%20is%20a%20missed%20opportunity%20for%20eliminating%20this%20regressive%20matrimonial%20remedy%20from%20the%20statute%20book%2C%20thereby%20promoting%20gender%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENon-recognition%20of%20rights%20of%20trans%20and%20queer%20persons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClause%203(1)(j)%20of%20the%20Bill%20defines%20%E2%80%9Cperson%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Can%20individual%2C%20whether%20male%20or%20female%2C%20and%20the%20expressions%20%E2%80%9Che%2Fshe%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Chis%2Fher%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cher%2Fhim%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cherself%2Fhimself%E2%80%9D%20shall%20be%20construed%20accordingly.%20The%20Bill%20is%20replete%20with%20references%20to%20son%20and%20daughter%2C%20husband%20and%20wife%2C%20brother%20and%20sister%2C%20completely%20excluding%20the%20transgender%20persons%20from%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20Bill%20and%20the%20rights%20and%20protections%20it%20may%20accord.%C2%A0%20Alternatively%2C%20it%20compels%20them%20to%20adhere%20to%20their%20gender%20assigned%20at%20birth%2C%20which%20violates%20their%20constitutionally%20guaranteed%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F193543132%2F%5C%22%3ENALSA%20judgment%20of%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%20recognised%20the%20rights%20of%20transgender%20persons%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthc.nic.in%2FCentral%2520Governmental%2520Acts%2FTransgender%2520Persons%2520(Protection%2520of%2520Rights)%2520Act%2C%25202019.pdf%5C%22%3ETransgender%20Persons%20(Protection%20of%20Rights)%20Act%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%20provided%20statutory%20recognition%20of%20the%20same.%20In%202019%2C%20through%20the%20judgment%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F188806075%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EArun%20Kumar%20vs.%20Inspector%20General%20of%20Registration%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%20recognised%20a%20trans%20woman%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbride%E2%80%9D%20within%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act.%20The%20right%20of%20transgender%20persons%20to%20have%20a%20valid%20heterosexual%20marriage%20was%20affirmed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202023%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F129202312%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESupriyo%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20the%20marriage%20equality%20judgment.%20The%20Uttarakhand%20UCC%20Bill%20is%20oblivious%20to%20these%20legal%20developments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20also%20implies%20that%20inheritance%20among%20%3Cem%3Ehijra%3C%2Fem%3E%20communities%20would%20continue%20to%20be%20governed%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3Eguru-chhela%20parampara%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20is%20judicially%20recognised%20through%20judgments%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdocfragment%2F490695%2F%3FformInput%3Dshashi%2520kumar%2520v%2520subodh%2520kumar%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIlliyas%20and%20Others%20vs.%20Badshah%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftranslaw.clpr.org.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F12%2FSweety_Eunuch_vs_General_Public_22062016__HPHCHP2016141016151351109COM53458.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESweety%20vs.%20General%20Public%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20high%20courts%20respectively.%20Inheritance%20practices%20among%20other%20communities%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3Earavani%2C%20kothi%2C%20shiv%20shakti%2C%20jogappa%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekinnar%3C%2Fem%3E%20would%20also%20continue%20without%20being%20affected%20by%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20does%20not%20include%20marriages%20among%20queer%20persons%2C%20as%20clause%204%20of%20the%20Bill%20states%20that%20a%20marriage%20maybe%20solemnised%20between%20a%20man%20and%20a%20woman%2C%20after%20they%20fulfil%20the%20criteria%20laid%20down%20in%20the%20clause.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20Bill%20does%20not%20recognise%20live-in%20relationships%20among%20same%20sex%20couples%2C%20as%20clause%203(4)(b)%20defines%20a%20live-in%20relationship%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20relationship%20between%20a%20man%20and%20a%20woman%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20Thus%2C%20only%20heterosexual%20relationships%20and%20marriages%20are%20recognised%20in%20this%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3ESupriyo%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20majority%20judgment%20said%20that%20the%20State%20is%20duty-bound%20to%20ensure%20that%20there%20are%20no%20impediments%20for%20queer%20couples%20to%20enjoy%20the%20rights%20flowing%20from%20all%20previous%20judgments%20as%20well%20as%20the%20right%20to%20relationship%20as%20defined%20in%20this%20judgment.%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20mandated%20the%20legislature%20to%20enable%20these%20rights.%20The%20Uttarakhand%20legislature%20had%20the%20first%20opportunity%20to%20follow%20these%20directives%2C%20but%20it%20failed%20to%20do%20so%2C%20by%20completely%20ignoring%20the%20rights%20and%20concerns%20of%20queer%20and%20trans%20communities%20as%20if%20such%20communities%20do%20not%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20non-recognition%20of%20queer%20marriages%20in%20law%2C%20various%20courts%20have%20provided%20protection%20orders%20to%20queer%20couples%20whose%20families%20and%20communities%20opposed%20their%20relationship.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%202020%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fahmedabad%2Fcourt-comes-to-rescue-of-gujarat-polices-first-lesbian-couple%2Farticleshow%2F77296590.cms%5C%22%3EGujarat%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20reportedly%20provided%20protection%20to%20a%20lesbian%20couple%20who%20underwent%20police%20training%20together%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2Fdelhi-hc-grants-protection-to-lesbian-woman-forcibly-married-threatened-with-conversion-therapy%5C%22%3Ethe%20Delhi%20high%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20lesbian%20couple%20who%20fled%20from%20the%20state%20of%20Rajasthan%20to%20Delhi%2C%20fearing%20threat%20to%20their%20life%2C%20liberty%20and%20security%20from%20their%20parents%3B%20in%202021%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Ftamil-nadu%2F2021%2Fmar%2F30%2Fmadras-high-court-orders-counselling-to-parents-of-lesbian-couple-who-threatened-duo-2283569.html%5C%22%3EMadras%20high%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20reportedly%20directed%20parents%20of%20a%20lesbian%20couple%20to%20be%20sent%20for%20counselling%20because%20they%20threatened%20the%20couple%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fother-states%2Fallahabad-high-court-orders-protection-for-same-sex-couple%2Farticle33700145.ece%5C%22%3EAllahabad%20high%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20provided%20protection%20to%20lesbian%20couples%20in%20more%20than%20one%20instance.%20The%20focus%20of%20the%20Bill%20on%20heterosexuality%20in%20marriage%20and%20live-in%20relationships%20flies%20in%20the%20face%20of%20such%20jurisprudential%20developments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20Bill%20ought%20to%20have%20addressed%20familial%20violence%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20queer%20and%20trans%20persons.%20Last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpucl.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2FCombined_all_2_compressed.pdf%5C%22%3Ea%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20findings%20of%20a%20closed%20door%20hearing%20on%20the%20issue%20was%20published%2C%20based%20on%20the%20testimony%20of%2031%20queer%20and%20trans%20persons%20from%20across%20India.%20It%20found%20that%20natal%20family%20violence%20is%20often%20normalised%2C%20ignored%20by%20the%20law%20and%20legal%20institutions%2C%20justified%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpunitive%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Ccorrective%E2%80%9D%20measures%20for%20perceived%20transgressions%20of%20gender%20and%20sexuality%20norms%2C%20and%20facilitates%20surveillance%20and%20control%20by%20the%20natal%20family%20in%20the%20name%20of%20protecting%20its%20%E2%80%9Chonour%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Bill%20does%20great%20disservice%20to%20queer%20and%20trans%20persons%20in%20ignoring%20this%20ground%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20sets%20no%20limit%20to%20the%20quantum%20of%20property%20that%20can%20be%20willed%20away%20in%20clause%2061.%20Thus%2C%20a%20parent%20may%20completely%20disinherit%20their%20child%20based%20on%20the%20child%E2%80%99s%20gender%20identity%20or%20sexual%20orientation.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.pib.gov.in%2Fdocuments%2Frlink%2F2018%2Faug%2Fp201883101.pdf%5C%22%3E2018%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%20had%20recommended%20that%2C%20drawing%20from%20Muslim%20law%2C%20some%20portion%20of%20the%20property%20must%20be%20fixed%20by%20law%20for%20the%20dependants%20of%20the%20deceased%20under%20all%20family%20laws.%20This%20recommendation%20has%20been%20completely%20ignored%20in%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20cumulative%20analysis%20of%20the%20three%20set%20of%20provisions%20discussed%20above%20indicate%20that%20the%20Bill%20embeds%20and%20enforces%20heterosexuality%20in%20its%20provisions%2C%20ignores%20ramifications%20of%20these%20provisions%20on%20women%20(including%20queer%20and%20trans%20women)%20and%20reinforces%20natal%20family%E2%80%99s%20control%20over%20choice%20marriages%20and%20live-in%20relationships%20among%20adults.%20It%20criminalises%20adult%20consensual%20relationships%20that%20are%20not%20registered%20and%20infantilises%20them%3B%20simultaneously%2C%20it%20turns%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20natal%20family%E2%80%99s%20violence%20on%20and%20imposition%20of%20their%20choice%20of%20partner%20on%20their%20children%20through%20forced%20marriages.%20Its%20protectionist%20approach%20in%20mandating%20registration%20of%20live-in%20relationships%20is%20hardly%20empowering%20for%20women%3B%20in%20fact%2C%20it%20exposes%20them%20to%20the%20wrath%20of%20the%20combined%20forces%20of%20family%2C%20community%20and%20state%20agencies%20and%20further%20disempowers%20them.%20As%20such%2C%20the%20claim%20that%20a%20UCC%20promotes%20gender%20justice%20is%20a%20hollow%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20discussed%20above%20ignore%20constitutional%20guarantees%20of%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20judicial%20developments%2C%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%20and%20concerns%2C%20and%20public%20discourse%20in%20India%20and%20elsewhere.%20It%20is%20a%20missed%20opportunity%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20State%20to%20enact%20a%20truly%20gender%20just%2C%20inclusive%2C%20progressive%20and%20equitable%20family%20law.%C2%A0%20If%20this%20Bill%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20blueprint%20for%20a%20UCC%20to%20be%20enacted%20in%20other%20states%20and%20at%20the%20national%20level%2C%20further%20deliberations%20by%20a%20Standing%20Committee%20of%20the%20state%20legislature%20as%20well%20as%20through%20public%20discourse%20%C2%A0are%20certainly%20warranted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr.%20Saumya%20Uma%20is%20a%20Professor%20at%20Jindal%20Global%20Law%20School%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20and%20heads%20its%20Centre%20for%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Rights.%20She%20teaches%2C%20writes%20and%20speaks%20at%20the%20intersections%20of%20gender%2C%20human%20rights%20and%20the%20law.%20The%20opinions%20expressed%20in%20this%20article%20are%20her%20own.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707460224000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09110758%2Flewis-j-goetz-67heLkXJ