%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efossilized%20bone%3C%2Fa%3E%20looks%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20he%20came%20across%20the%20boulder%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efrom%20the%20shape%2C%20he%20recognized%20it%20was%20likely%20a%20skull%2C%20and%20he%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20friend%2C%20hauled%20the%2070-pound%20rock%20back%20to%20his%20parents'%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESheperd%2C%20who's%20currently%20in%20medical%20school%2C%20credits%20the%20paleontologist%20at%20the%20Santa%20Cruz%20Museum%20of%20Natural%20History%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewith%20identifying%20many%20of%20his%20fossil%20finds%20and%20connecting%20him%20with%20marine%20mammal%20fossil%20expert%20Robert%20Boessenecker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224848%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20holding%20a%20brownish%20walrus%20skull%20that's%20about%205%20million%20years%20old%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c4025b43bb77284ba4c5f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223700%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECo-authors%20Robert%20Boessenecker%20and%20Sarah%20Boessenecker%20hold%20the%20Valenictus%20walrus%20skull.%3Cp%3ERobert%20Boessenecker%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEleven%20years%20after%20Sheperd%20found%20it%2C%20Boessenecker%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffish-do-not-exist-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enamed%20the%20newly-identified%3C%2Fa%3E%20walrus%20species%20Valenictus%20sheperdi%2C%20after%20Sheperd's%20last%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20fossil%20was%20found%20by%20a%2013-year-old%20kid%2C%26quot%3B%20Boessenecker%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20really%20remarkable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20Boessenecker%20used%20to%20comb%20the%20same%20beach%20looking%20for%20fossils.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20going%20there%20since%20I%20was%2015%2C%20so%20Forrest%20got%20luckier%20than%20I%20did%2C%26q